VALUES
(42, 21, 9, 41, 13, 7, 8, NULL, 'Connection of End Times Warnings', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of wars and troubles as precursors to the end times. They encourage believers not to be troubled by these events, indicating they are part of a larger divine plan.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 9, 23, 51, 12, 13, 'be not terrified', 'Fear and Comfort in Adversity', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of not being afraid in the face of turmoil. Luke encourages believers not to be terrified by wars, while Isaiah reassures them of God''s comfort against fear of oppressors.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 9, 42, 21, 18, 19, 'be not terrified', 'Connection of Fear and Patience', 'This connection highlights the theme of not being terrified amidst turmoil, as seen in both passages. While wars and commotions may cause fear, the assurance of safety and the call for patience in the face of adversity are emphasized.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 9, 19, 27, 1, 3, 'be not terrified', 'Fear in Times of Conflict', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of fearlessness in the face of conflict. Luke 21:9 encourages believers not to be terrified by wars, while Psalms 27:1-3 expresses confidence and lack of fear despite the presence of enemies and war.', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 9, 19, 46, 1, 2, 'be not terrified', 'Fear in Times of Trouble', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of not fearing during tumultuous times. Luke 21:9 mentions ''wars and commotions,'' while Psalms 46:1-2 reassures that God is a ''very present help in trouble.''', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 10, 41, 13, 8, 8, 'nation shall rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom', 'Connection of Eschatological Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the rise of nations and kingdoms against each other, indicating a shared theme of conflict in the end times. This connection highlights the prophetic nature of both texts regarding future turmoil.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 10, 44, 2, 19, 20, 'nation shall rise against nation', 'Connection of Signs and Nations', 'This connection highlights the theme of upheaval and cosmic signs preceding significant events. Both passages emphasize turmoil, with nations rising against nations and wonders in the heavens indicating impending judgment.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 10, 14, 15, 5, 6, 'nation shall rise against nation', 'Conflict Among Nations', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of nations rising against each other, highlighting a time of great turmoil and conflict. Luke 21:10''s mention of ''nation shall rise against nation'' parallels 2 Chronicles 15:5-6''s description of ''nation was destroyed of nation.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 10, 38, 14, 13, 13, 'nation shall rise against nation', 'Conflict and Tumult in Prophecy', 'Both passages emphasize rising conflict among nations and individuals. Luke 21:10 speaks of nations rising against each other, while Zechariah 14:13 describes neighbors turning against one another, highlighting a theme of turmoil.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 10, 58, 12, 27, 27, 'nation shall rise against nation', 'Conflict and Stability in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of upheaval and the eventual establishment of enduring truths. Both passages emphasize the contrast between temporary conflicts and lasting stability.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 10, 23, 19, 2, 2, 'kingdom against kingdom', 'Conflict Among Nations', 'Both passages emphasize conflict between nations and kingdoms. The phrase ''kingdom against kingdom'' appears in both, highlighting a theme of internal strife and warfare.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 10, 38, 14, 2, 3, 'Nation shall rise against nation', 'Conflict Among Nations', 'Both passages emphasize the rising conflict among nations, with Luke highlighting nations rising against each other and Zechariah depicting a specific battle against Jerusalem. This connection highlights the theme of national strife and divine intervention in such conflicts.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 11, 40, 24, 29, 30, 'great signs shall there be from heaven', 'Signs of Cosmic Disturbance', 'Both passages emphasize cosmic signs and upheaval. Luke mentions ''great signs'' from heaven, while Matthew describes the sun darkening and stars falling, indicating a connection in the theme of apocalyptic events.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 11, 42, 21, 25, 27, 'great signs shall there be from heaven', 'Signs of Distress and Fear', 'Both passages emphasize signs and distress occurring on earth, including natural disasters and fear among people. The mention of ''great signs'' in the first passage connects to the ''signs in the sun, and in the moon, and in the stars'' in the second passage.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 12, 60, 4, 12, 14, 'for my name’s sake', 'Persecution and Suffering Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the experience of persecution for Christ''s name. Luke 21:12 speaks of being delivered up and persecuted, while 1 Peter 4:14 highlights being reproached for Christ''s name, linking the themes of suffering and glory.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 12, 40, 10, 16, 25, 'delivering you up to the synagogues', 'Persecution of Followers', 'Both passages emphasize the persecution that followers of Jesus will face, including being delivered up to councils and rulers. They highlight the challenges and dangers of discipleship, reinforcing the idea that followers will endure suffering for Jesus'' name.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 12, 40, 23, 34, 36, 'persecute you, delivering you up to the synagogues', 'Persecution of Righteous Figures', 'Both passages emphasize the persecution of prophets and righteous individuals. Luke mentions being brought before synagogues and rulers, while Matthew describes killing and scourging in synagogues.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 12, 41, 13, 9, 13, 'for my name’s sake', 'Persecution for Christ''s Name', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of persecution faced by believers for the sake of Christ. They describe being delivered up to councils and synagogues, highlighting the trials and betrayals that followers will endure.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 12, 42, 11, 49, 51, 'persecute you, delivering you up', 'Persecution of Prophets and Followers', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of persecution faced by God''s messengers. Luke 21:12 speaks of followers being persecuted, while Luke 11:49-51 discusses the slaying and persecution of prophets, linking the experiences of Jesus'' followers with those of earlier prophets.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 12, 43, 15, 20, 20, 'persecute you', 'Persecution of Followers', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of persecution faced by Jesus'' followers. Luke 21:12 speaks of being persecuted and brought before rulers, while John 15:20 states that if they have persecuted Jesus, they will also persecute His followers.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 12, 43, 16, 2, 3, NULL, 'Persecution of Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the persecution believers will face, including being put out of synagogues and brought before rulers. They highlight the misunderstanding of those who inflict such harm, believing they serve God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 13, 50, 1, 12, 12, 'turn to you for a testimony', 'Testimony and Furtherance of Gospel', 'This connection highlights how both passages emphasize the idea that experiences, whether trials or challenges, can serve a greater purpose in advancing the gospel. In Luke, the phrase ''turn to you for a testimony'' suggests that difficult situations can provide opportunities for witness, which is echoed in Philippians where Paul notes that his circumstances have contributed to the ''furtherance of the gospel.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 13, 50, 1, 28, 28, 'for a testimony', 'Testimony and Adversity Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of facing adversaries and how such experiences serve as a testimony of faith. Both passages emphasize that challenges can lead to a demonstration of salvation and divine support.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 13, 53, 1, 5, 5, 'turn to you for a testimony', 'Suffering and Testimony Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of suffering as a means of testimony and validation of faith. Both passages emphasize that enduring trials can lead to a greater purpose in God''s kingdom.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 13, 52, 3, 3, 4, 'turn to you for a testimony', 'Afflictions as a Testimony', 'This connection highlights the theme of suffering as a means of testimony. Both passages emphasize that tribulations are expected and serve a purpose in the believer''s life.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 14, 41, 13, 11, 11, 'not to meditate before what ye shall answer', 'Connection of Guidance in Trials', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of not premeditating one''s response in times of trial. They instruct believers to rely on divine guidance during moments of persecution.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 14, 42, 12, 11, 12, 'not to meditate before what ye shall answer', 'Divine Guidance in Speech', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of not preparing answers in advance. They highlight reliance on the Holy Spirit for guidance during challenging situations.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 14, 40, 10, 19, 20, 'not to meditate before what ye shall answer', 'Connection of Divine Guidance', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of not preparing answers in advance, suggesting reliance on divine inspiration during challenging times. This connection highlights the assurance that the Spirit will provide the necessary words.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 21, 15, 24, 1, 9, 9, NULL, 'Divine Empowerment of Speech', 'This connection highlights the theme of God empowering individuals with words. Both passages emphasize the idea of divine intervention in providing wisdom and speech to confront adversaries.', 'theme', 0.5589999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
